Jeremy,

a) HPFS is an *IFS*, that is an INSTALLABLE FILE SYSTEM; it is an EXTERNAL
  add-on.  It is *NOT* part of the OS proper.  The CDFS is an IFS
  for CD-ROMs.  The closest analogy is a mountable Unix file system.

b) Please list the "some other stuff" in Warp that is "16-bit as well".

c)  USER and GDI in W95 are NOT external addons.  Due to the 16-bit Mutex
  in W95 the 16-bit code in W95 *IS* a big deal.

